item.title: What went wrong for Kentucky basketball this season?
item.description: The bluebloods of college basketball were not their usual selves in the 2020-2021 season, Kentucky being the most disappointing of them all. The Wildcats went 9-16 this year and finished 8-9 in conference play, missing the NCAA tournament for the first time since 2013. To begin looking at what went wrong for Kentucky this season, letâ€™s start by grabbing the games logs for each team of the 2020-2021 season.
